com.xtructure.xneat.genetics
Interface NEATGenome<D>

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<XIdObject>, EvolutionObject, GeneticsObject, Genome<D>, XIdObject
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractNEATGenome, NEATGenomeImpl
public interface NEATGenome<D>
extends Genome<D>

The NEATGenome interface is for individuals on which evolution is to be applied. It carries an arbitrary payload for it's chromosome data. It's primary attributes are fitness, complexity, evaluation count, and death mark. As part of the NEAT algorithm, it also has species id attribute.

Author:
Luis Guimbarda
